1 — Data loading & cleaning
===========================

Raw dataset loaded: 195 rows × 35 columns (world-data-2023.csv)

Dropped 6 non-predictive identifier columns:
  Abbreviation, Calling Code, Capital/Major City, Currency-Code, Largest city, Official language

Removed 5 rows with near-empty data (Vatican City, Nauru, Palestinian National Authority, North Macedonia, Eswatini)

Shape after cleanup: 190 rows × 29 columns

Renamed 28 columns for consistency; cleaned percentage, currency, and comma-formatted numeric fields.

Missing data flags:
  - Minimum_Wage: 21.05% missing
  - Tax_Revenue_pct: 11.58% missing
  - Overall cell missingness: 3.08% (193/6270)
  - Created 4 binary missingness flags for downstream use


2 — Feature engineering
=======================

Created 24 engineered features across 5 domains:
  - Economic (6): GDP_per_Capita, Log_GDP, Log_Population, Economic_Stress_Index,
      Inflation_Unemployment_Pressure, Tax_Burden_Index
  - Healthcare (4): Healthcare_Stability_Score, Mortality_Pressure_Index,
      Physician_Access_Score, Healthcare_Access_Gap
  - Education & Workforce (4): Human_Capital_Index, Workforce_Stability_Score,
      Education_Pipeline, Education_Gap_Index
  - Demographic (5): Urbanization_Rate, Population_Pressure_Index,
      Dependency_Ratio_Proxy, Military_Burden, Abs_Latitude
  - Environment (5): CO2_per_Capita, CO2_per_GDP, Environmental_Pressure_Index,
      Resource_Land_Balance, Fuel_Cost_Pressure

Stability score constructed from z-score signals:
  Positive: Life_Expectancy, Physicians_per_1000, Primary_Education_pct,
            Tertiary_Education_pct, GDP_per_Capita
  Negative: Infant_Mortality, Maternal_Mortality
  Score range: -5.034 to +5.673

Target labels created with balanced classes:
  Class 0 (Stable):  63 countries (33.3%)
  Class 1 (Watch):   63 countries (33.3%)
  Class 2 (At-Risk): 63 countries (33.3%)

Note: 1 row dropped due to NaN stability score.
Final featured dataset: 189 rows × 59 columns

Removed 10 leaky features (direct signal components) + Country column before modelling.


3 — Train / test split
======================

Stratified split — 80/20 on 189 samples:
  X_train: 151 × 47  |  y_train: 151
  X_test:   38 × 47  |  y_test:   38
  Class balance preserved in both splits.


4 — Model training
==================

Three models trained on 151 samples × 47 features:
  - LogisticRegression  (interpretable baseline)   — trained in 0.02s
  - RandomForest        (nonlinear benchmark)       — trained in 0.50s
  - XGBoost             (primary production model)  — trained in 1.68s

XGBoost used sample weights (min 0.987, max 1.007).
All 3 models trained successfully.


5 — Cross-validation (5-fold stratified)
========================================

Model              Accuracy          Macro F1          Weighted F1       Recall (macro)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
XGBoost            0.808 ± 0.044     0.809 ± 0.042     0.809 ± 0.042     0.807 ± 0.044  *best
RandomForest       0.802 ± 0.046     0.804 ± 0.046     0.804 ± 0.046     0.801 ± 0.047
LogisticRegression 0.788 ± 0.058     0.789 ± 0.056     0.789 ± 0.056     0.787 ± 0.058

Best model (CV): XGBoost — Macro F1: 0.8086 ± 0.0420


6 — Held-out test set evaluation (38 samples)
=============================================

Model              Accuracy   Macro Precision  Macro Recall  Macro F1   At-Risk Recall
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
XGBoost            0.8158     0.8250           0.8205        0.8042     0.9231         *best
LogisticRegression 0.7895     0.7878           0.7927        0.7799     0.9231
RandomForest       0.7895     0.7878           0.7927        0.7799     0.9231

Summary:
  Best model    : XGBoost
  Test accuracy : 81.6%
  Macro F1      : 0.804
  At-Risk recall: 92.3%


7 — Top feature importances
===========================

XGBoost top features:
  Birth_Rate (0.132), Education_Pipeline (0.080), GDP_per_Capita (0.078),
  Population_Pressure_Index (0.053), Healthcare_Access_Gap (0.046),
  Fertility_Rate (0.039), Dependency_Ratio_Proxy (0.039), Education_Gap_Index (0.034)

RandomForest top features:
  Education_Pipeline (0.126), Birth_Rate (0.106), Population_Pressure_Index (0.084),
  GDP_per_Capita (0.081), CO2_per_Capita (0.071), Fertility_Rate (0.068),
  Healthcare_Access_Gap (0.066), Dependency_Ratio_Proxy (0.052)

LogisticRegression top features:
  Education_Pipeline (0.702), Human_Capital_Index (0.598), Education_Gap_Index (0.544),
  Forested_Area_pct (0.514), GDP_per_Capita (0.451), Agricultural_Land_pct (0.449)

Note: Education_Pipeline and GDP_per_Capita rank highly across all three models,
consistent with domain expectations for geopolitical stability prediction.


